HEADWORD: Djerrid
<hw>Djer*rid"</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr></mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>djerid</ets>, fr. Ar.
See <er>Jereed</er>.]</ety> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A blunt javelin used in
military games in Moslem countries.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A game
played with it.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>jereed</asp>,
<asp>jerrid</asp>, etc.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

